cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with resource allocation and power allocation, which are related to information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the design of dual-mode base stations, which are part of networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper considers the system energy consumption and load, which are related to systems and control. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper takes into account different types of user applications, which may include multimedia applications. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper does not directly deal with hardware architecture, but the design of dual-mode base stations may involve hardware considerations.
